{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-13235/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-13235"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:32:35"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed, zoom"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Woman and man sit on the couch, facing each other and holding hands"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-13235","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-13235"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/canvas/1/bd547f91-059b-43a8-bd8b-f5529cf3edb4","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:07:26.325Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The wedding dress, a piece already connected with his deceased mother, whose wedding dress was Reynolds’s first design, stands in the foreground in an almost ghostly manner. It represents both the specter of his mother, whose role Alma has now fulfilled through her caretaking, and the ways his work consumed his life. As the camera moves closer to Reynolds and Alma, the dress begins to fade from view. He now turns his attention entirely to Alma, asking her to marry him. His mother’s ghost disappears, allowing Alma to take her place.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13235/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:37.40259740259688,38.18181818181756,1581.8181818181818,944.4155844155845"}}}]}]}]}